parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crank positioning sensor can cause the engine to die or not start, leading to potential accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The engine dies or won't start
the engine cranks but won't start
the engine starts after a few minutes
the engine dies again after a short period.

loss of coolant

headaches
dizziness
stomach aches
nausea
and extreme fatigue.

symptoms: Headaches
dizziness
stomach aches
nausea
and extreme fatigue
respiratory illnesses such as reactive airways disease.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Worn and grooved brake rotors can lead to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Brake rotors are excessively worn or grooved
vehicle takes longer to stop
spongy brake pedal
loud noises when applying brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the automatic transmission to shift properly can cause loss of control, accidents, and engine damage.
symptoms: Transmission hesitates or fails to shift from first to second gear
delayed or incomplete shifting
unusual noises or vibrations when shifting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the ABS system can cause loss of control, accidents, and increased stopping distances.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor
vehicle fails to stop
ABS sensor malfunction
unusual noises or vibrations when applying brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic transmission can cause the vehicle to seize or become immobile, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents. Additionally, the sudden failure of the transmission can cause damage to other components, resulting in costly repairs.
symptoms: The transmission seizes or becomes stuck
the vehicle is unable to move forward or backward
the transmission shifts gears slowly
a rattling noise is heard inside the vehicle
a bump is felt inside the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Misalignment of the rear suspension can cause uneven tire wear, reduced vehicle stability, and affect overall handling, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Roaring sound from the rear
uneven tire wear on the inside tread
knocking or clunking noise from the rear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Abnormal noises and vibrations from the front end can indicate a problem with the suspension or steering system, which can affect vehicle handling and safety.
symptoms: Rubbing or knocking sound when traveling in the morning or backing out
constant knocking in the front end while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt latching mechanism can lead to the seat belt becoming unbuckled while the vehicle is in motion, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle will not latch properly
the seat belt will not click into place
the seat belt becomes unbuckled while the vehicle is in motion
the seat belt is difficult to latch
the seat belt is intermittently functional.
